Stopped by at 9pm on a Friday night when I was still hungry after walking around NYC for the day.  Busy intersection across from the Subway Green 6 line.  Open window facing the street.  A few counter places to sit next to the window.  Excellent value for $4.25 a slice for a bacon covered cheesy fresh masterpiece.  Sam’s “Famous” Pizza deserves its middle name.   If you want it spicy, add some peppers.  Personally, i wouldn’t mess with it.  Appears to be a neighborhood treasure, not the place for quiet sit-down meal, but the place to go when you need a quick bite to satisfy hunger and the taste buds.
